The paper deals with the security of genomic data, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the need for specialized techniques for securing genomic data, which could be related to database systems (cs.DB). The analysis of the effectiveness of GenoGuard in providing long-term security for genomic data could also be relevant to the field of cyber-physical systems (cs.CY). The paper uses statistical methods to analyze the security guarantees provided by GenoGuard, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and information theory (cs.SI).
